CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 9, 1959, pg. 2 reads: "Reward for Service - WIlling volunteers of the last seven months at the Friendship Community Center, 181 Robinson St., were "pinned" during the annual open house May Night celebration. The affair is one extension program of Soho Community House, directed by Harry D. Bray.  in above picture, left to right, are Mrs. Ann Patton, Mrs. Ella Powell, Miss Evelyn Beale, Miss Bertha Kin, all of Terrace Village II - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of volunteers, from left: Ann Patton, Ella Powell, Evelyn Beale, and Bertha Kin, gathered around table with dishes in Friendship Community Center during May Night celebration
